HEADWORD: Tellurite
<hw>Tel"lu*rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A salt of tellurous acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Oxide of tellurium. It occurs
sparingly in tufts of white or yellowish crystals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tellurium</ent>⟦br⟧
